wiki.summary: "Sticky" is the second digital single by South Korean girl group KISS OF LIFE, released on July 1, 2024, through S2 Entertainment. The song showcases an Afrobeat rhythm, marking a stylistic shift from the group's earlier hip-hop and retro-inspired tracks. Lyrically, "Sticky" delves into themes of possessive love and the fears associated with it, with the members expressing concerns about being abandoned while conveying deep affection for their partner. wiki.content: "Sticky" is the second digital single by South Korean girl group KISS OF LIFE, released on July 1, 2024, through S2 Entertainment. The song showcases an Afrobeat rhythm, marking a stylistic shift from the group's earlier hip-hop and retro-inspired tracks. Lyrically, "Sticky" delves into themes of possessive love and the fears associated with it, with the members expressing concerns about being abandoned while conveying deep affection for their partner. The track has been praised for its suitability as a summer anthem, featuring flowy, melodic elements that align with the season's vibe. Upon release, "Sticky" achieved significant chart success, reaching number 3 on South Korea's Circle Digital Chart and number 87 on the Billboard Global 200. The accompanying music video, released simultaneously, features vibrant and refreshing visuals that complement the song's upbeat nature. Read more on Last.fm.
